## 6. Steli Efti (Close)

**Background:** Close CEO; hundreds of thousands of cold calls; evangelist for **reach rate**, follow-up, and funnel diagnostics.

### 1. Craft High-Performing Email Sequences (Webinar)
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XH2SHKREPDY  
- **Published:** December 5, 2018  
- **Why valuable:** Still one of the best public walkthroughs of **full sequence architecture** (intervals, goals per email, break-up email).  
- **Key lessons:** One purpose per email; break-up email often highest-converting; when tokens vs. true personalization; maintain opens on emails 2–6 with fresh subject lines.  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** Direct template for SaaS sequence design in Close/Apollo/Outreach.

### 2. How to Build a Solo SaaS Sales Machine (MicroConf 2015)
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8PuKwEfXZqc  
- **Published:** March 26, 2020 (talk originally 2015)  
- **Why valuable:** Founder-grade outbound—emails, follow-up obsession, and building pipeline without a big SDR team.  
- **Key lessons:** 90% of success is follow-up; short emails win; subject line gets equal effort as body; cold outreach as learning engine; pragmatic channel choice (not dogmatic).  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** How early-stage SaaS got first customers via outbound—still applicable for founder-led sales.

### 3. Sales Alchemy — How to Turn a Dry Pipeline into Golden Opportunities
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Sx6e-AIEeaY  
- **Published:** April 28, 2021 (recorded 2017)  
- **Why valuable:** Addresses **pipeline revival**—reactivating dead leads systematically.  
- **Key lessons:** Revisit dead leads (timing may have changed); activity quality leads, pipeline lags; re-engage with new value, not “checking in”; build revival cadence as standard process.  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** Extends ROI of prior prospecting investment—critical for lean SaaS teams.

