## 8. Max Altschuler (Sales Hacker / GTMfund)

**Background:** Sales Hacker founder; **Hacking Sales** author; architect of modern sales cadences and tech stack.

### 1. How To Hack Sales (Close More Deals, Easier) — Salesman Podcast
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nfHBysGMenc  
- **Published:** May 23, 2016  
- **Why valuable:** Foundational **10/80/10 email structure** and scalable high-touch outbound from Udemy/Sales Hacker era.  
- **Key lessons:** 10% personalized intro, 80% segmented body, 10% personalized outro; balance scale + relevance; stack sales tech on CRM; track opens/replies by variant.  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** Template for scaling outbound without losing relevance—still used in SaaS SDR playbooks.

### 2. Everything Modern Sales and Outbound with Max Altschuler
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MtOB0W20Wjs  
- **Published:** October 6, 2020  
- **Why valuable:** Signal-based vs. schedule-based selling; multi-channel imperative; metrics that matter.  
- **Key lessons:** Reach out on **signals**, not fixed cadence alone; orchestrate email + phone + social; measure pipeline/rep, not activity vanity; engagement platform + CRM both required.  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** Modern SaaS outbound operating model.

### 3. Early-Stage SaaS GTM with GTMfund’s GP Max Altschuler
- **URL:** https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9QQZd57NrdI  
- **Published:** May 31, 2024  
- **Why valuable:** Investor lens on **what outbound motions work** before scaling headcount.  
- **Key lessons:** Nail one narrow ICP first; founders should outbound before hiring SDRs; outbound = product feedback loop; document what works before scaling; use reply/objection data to refine positioning.  
- **B2B SaaS relevance:** Essential for Seed/Series A founders building first pipeline motion.

